@prefix :       <#> .
@prefix schema: <http://schema.org/> .
@prefix rdfs:   <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix xsd:    <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix onto:   <https://www.openlinksw.com/ontology/> .

# ── Self-describing document entity ──────────────────────────────────────────

<> a schema:CreativeWork ;
    schema:name "HowTo: SPARQL-Based Session Memory Loading"@en ;
    schema:description "Companion howto for preferences.ttl Steps 45 and 46. Specifies that agent-rdf-memory/index.ttl is the sole memory discovery index (MEMORY.md is not written to), and that SPARQL-based memory loading via elicited endpoint selection is the preferred alternative to sequential file reads at session initialization."@en ;
    schema:dateCreated "2026-06-14T00:00:00Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    schema:dateModified "2026-06-14T00:00:00Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    schema:about :HowToSparqlMemoryLoading .

# ── HowTo ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

:HowToSparqlMemoryLoading a schema:HowTo ;
    schema:name "SPARQL-Based Session Memory Loading with Endpoint Elicitation"@en ;
    schema:description "At session start, elicit a SPARQL endpoint from the user and load preferences, howto steps, and session context via SPARQL query rather than sequential file reads. Fallback to file reads if endpoint is unreachable."@en ;
    schema:step :stepNoMemoryMd,
                :stepEndpointElicitation,
                :stepSparqlQueries,
                :stepNamedGraphConvention,
                :stepFallback .

# ── Steps ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

:stepNoMemoryMd a schema:HowToStep ;
    schema:position 1 ;
    schema:name "Do not write to MEMORY.md"@en ;
    schema:text """agent-rdf-memory/index.ttl is the canonical discovery index. The platform's .claude/projects/.../memory/MEMORY.md is redundant and must not be written to proactively.

All memory writes go exclusively to:
  - agent-rdf-memory/preferences.ttl
  - agent-rdf-memory/howto/<topic>.ttl
  - agent-rdf-memory/core.ttl
  - agent-rdf-memory/index.ttl
  - agent-rdf-memory/sessions/YYYY-MM-DD-{llm-id}-{agent-env}.ttl
  - agent-rdf-memory/entities/*.ttl
  - agent-rdf-memory/projects/<name>.ttl

If the platform writes to MEMORY.md autonomously, do not delete or correct it — just do not write to it proactively."""@en .

:stepEndpointElicitation a schema:HowToStep ;
    schema:position 2 ;
    schema:name "Determine memory loading path at session start"@en ;
    schema:text """At session initialization, check the most recent session TTL (via index.ttl pointers) for onto:usedSparqlEndpoint or onto:usedFileReads.

If a stored preference is found: reuse it — skip elicitation.

If no stored preference exists (first session), present this elicitation:

  "Memory loading preference:
   (1) File reads  [default — no Virtuoso required]
   (2) SPARQL — localhost:8890/sparql  [local Virtuoso, file:// URIs]
   (3) SPARQL — other endpoint / other URI"

File reads (option 1) is the pre-selected default. It is overridden if the user actively chooses SPARQL or any other method via elicitation. The elicitation occurs on every first session — the default does not silently apply without presenting the choice.

For option 2, the agent constructs file:// URIs from the known agent-rdf-memory/ path:
  file:///Users/kidehen/Documents/Management/Development/ai-agent-skills/agent-rdf-memory/preferences.ttl
  (and equivalents for core.ttl, index.ttl, howto/*.ttl)

For option 3, the user supplies the endpoint URL and the base URI for the TTL files.

Record the selected path in the session TTL as onto:usedSparqlEndpoint (SPARQL) or onto:usedFileReads "true"^^xsd:boolean (file reads). Wait for selection before loading memory."""@en .

:stepSparqlQueries a schema:HowToStep ;
    schema:position 3 ;
    schema:name "SPARQL queries with Sponger pragmas for progressive memory loading"@en ;
    schema:text """Use two queries. The first bootstraps preferences and simultaneously sponges all companion howto files. The second harvests the loaded howto content.

── Query 1: Bootstrap ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

DEFINE get:soft "soft"
DEFINE input:grab-iri "{preferences-ttl-url}"
DEFINE input:grab-var "seeAlso"

SELECT ?pos ?name ?text ?seeAlso
FROM <{preferences-ttl-url}>
WHERE {
  ?step a <http://schema.org/HowToStep> ;
        <http://schema.org/position> ?pos ;
        <http://schema.org/name> ?name ;
        <http://schema.org/text> ?text .
  OPTIONAL { ?step <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#seeAlso> ?seeAlso }
}
ORDER BY ?pos

What this does:
  - input:grab-iri loads preferences.ttl into Virtuoso's quad store as a named graph before the query runs
  - get:soft "soft" uses the cached version on subsequent calls (avoids re-fetching on every session)
  - input:grab-var "seeAlso" tells the Sponger to dereference every ?seeAlso binding (i.e., every howto/*.ttl referenced from a step) and load them as named graphs during query execution
  - One round-trip loads preferences.ttl AND all companion howto files progressively

── Query 2: Harvest howto content ────────────────────────────────────────────

DEFINE get:soft "soft"

SELECT ?howto ?stepPos ?stepName ?stepText
FROM <{preferences-ttl-url}>
WHERE {
  ?step <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#seeAlso> ?howtoGraph .
  GRAPH ?howtoGraph {
    ?howto a <http://schema.org/HowTo> .
    ?howtoStep a <http://schema.org/HowToStep> ;
               <http://schema.org/position> ?stepPos ;
               <http://schema.org/name> ?stepName ;
               <http://schema.org/text> ?stepText .
  }
}
ORDER BY ?howtoGraph ?stepPos

What this does:
  - Queries across all named graphs loaded by Query 1
  - Retrieves the full step-by-step content from each howto/*.ttl
  - get:soft "soft" ensures cached graphs are reused without re-fetching

── Query 3: core.ttl facts ───────────────────────────────────────────────────

DEFINE get:soft "soft"
DEFINE input:grab-iri "{core-ttl-url}"

DESCRIBE <{core-ttl-url}>

── URL placeholder resolution ────────────────────────────────────────────────

{preferences-ttl-url} = "file:///Users/kidehen/Documents/Management/Development/ai-agent-skills/agent-rdf-memory/preferences.ttl"
{core-ttl-url}        = "file:///Users/kidehen/Documents/Management/Development/ai-agent-skills/agent-rdf-memory/core.ttl"

These are the standard values for local Virtuoso at localhost:8890/sparql.
The user substitutes a different URI only if the default file:// path does not match their setup
(e.g., different filesystem root, DAV upload, or remote public URL).

The Sponger fetches file:// URIs from the local filesystem and loads them as named graphs.
The named graph IRI is the file:// URI itself — use FROM <file:///…/preferences.ttl> in all queries."""@en .

:stepNamedGraphConvention a schema:HowToStep ;
    schema:position 4 ;
    schema:name "Named graph IRIs for agent-rdf-memory TTL files"@en ;
    schema:text """The named graph IRI is always the URI the Sponger was given to fetch.

Standard case (local Virtuoso, file:// URIs):
  FROM <file:///Users/kidehen/Documents/Management/Development/ai-agent-skills/agent-rdf-memory/preferences.ttl>
  FROM <file:///Users/kidehen/Documents/Management/Development/ai-agent-skills/agent-rdf-memory/core.ttl>

DAV case (files uploaded to Virtuoso's WebDAV store):
  FROM <http://localhost:8890/DAV/home/dba/agent-rdf-memory/preferences.ttl>

Remote / public case (URIBurner or GitHub raw):
  FROM <https://linkeddata.uriburner.com/DAV/home/kidehen/agent-rdf-memory/preferences.ttl>
  FROM <https://raw.githubusercontent.com/{owner}/{repo}/{branch}/agent-rdf-memory/preferences.ttl>

Always use an explicit FROM <named-graph-iri> to scope queries. Never query the default graph —
Virtuoso is a quad store and the default graph union may return stale or unrelated content."""@en .

:stepFallback a schema:HowToStep ;
    schema:position 5 ;
    schema:name "Fall back to sequential file reads if endpoint is unreachable"@en ;
    schema:text """If the selected SPARQL endpoint returns an error or empty results:
1. Report the failure: "SPARQL endpoint {url} unreachable — falling back to file reads."
2. Execute the standard CLAUDE.md startup protocol:
   - Read agent-rdf-memory/core.ttl
   - Read agent-rdf-memory/preferences.ttl
   - Read agent-rdf-memory/index.ttl
   - Follow index.ttl references to relevant session/project/entity files
3. Never fail silently — the user must know which loading path was taken."""@en .

# ── Registered Endpoints ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────

:EndpointLocalVirtuoso a schema:EntryPoint ;
    schema:name "Local Virtuoso SPARQL Endpoint"@en ;
    schema:url <http://localhost:8890/sparql> ;
    schema:description "Default local Virtuoso instance. Available when the user runs Virtuoso locally."@en .

:EndpointURIBurner a schema:EntryPoint ;
    schema:name "URIBurner SPARQL Endpoint"@en ;
    schema:url <https://linkeddata.uriburner.com/sparql> ;
    schema:description "Public Virtuoso-backed SPARQL endpoint hosted by OpenLink Software. Used when local Virtuoso is not running."@en .
